article_text:
Columbus Police are no longer searching for a missing boy in Columbus after he came home on Saturday.



Dylan Warren said he fell asleep at a friend's house.



Police were searching for him after he was last seen walking in the area or Talbrock Circle and Royalwood Drive around 6:30 p.m. Friday.

Stay with 10TV and refresh 10TV.com for more information as it becomes available.
